WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.480
While we hope that you have a seamless RStudio Cloud experience, occasionally things might

00:00:07.480 --> 00:00:09.680
not work as intended.

00:00:09.680 --> 00:00:15.200
Sometimes when we're working on a project, it may fail to load or become unresponsive.

00:00:15.200 --> 00:00:20.240
When this happens, we can relaunch the project by clicking on the three dots inside a circle

00:00:20.240 --> 00:00:23.959
to the left of the settings icon at the top of our project.

00:00:23.959 --> 00:00:29.440
Choosing the third option from this menu will relaunch our project.

00:00:29.440 --> 00:00:33.759
If this doesn't solve your issue, you can check to see if there are any broader issues

00:00:33.759 --> 00:00:35.799
with RStudio Cloud.

00:00:35.799 --> 00:00:41.040
To do this, expand the menu on the left to expose the current system status option in

00:00:41.040 --> 00:00:42.900
the help menu.

00:00:42.900 --> 00:00:47.799
Clicking this will tell us if RStudio Cloud is running as intended.

00:00:47.799 --> 00:00:52.799
If RStudio Cloud is operational and you are still running into issues, you may choose

00:00:52.799 --> 00:00:57.639
to post on our community forum or reach out to RStudio's technical support team.

